Hashing
Turns a password into random letters numbers and symbols.
One to one mapping - but you can make the hash different.
One way function.
Encrypting
Public Key - Something that everybody is allowed to know, used to encrypt things
Private key - Something that is used to decrypt things.
App needs to save key, if hacker hacks into the system they can get the key.
Ceaser Cipher
    Using a ceratain amount of letters to decode a message.
    Use 256 bits to make searching harder.
Plain Text
 Worst way to store passwords, as very easy to breach.
Salting
Adds random numbers and letters to back of password then hashes.
Hacking
    Looks for all common passwords to see if matches hash.
Slow Hashing
    Makes hackers guess less per/sec